{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":285,"text":"I'm going to talk about hackers."},{"time":2359,"text":"And the image that comes to your mind"},{"time":4279,"text":"when I say that word is probably not"},{"time":6738,"text":"of Benjamin Franklin,"},{"time":8255,"text":"but I'm going to explain to you why it should be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11443,"text":"The image that comes to your mind"},{"time":12920,"text":"is probably more likely of a pasty kid"},{"time":15606,"text":"sitting in a basement doing something mischievous,"},{"time":18122,"text":"or of a shady criminal who is\ntrying to steal your identity,"},{"time":22257,"text":"or of an international rogue"},{"time":25280,"text":"with a political agenda."},{"time":27991,"text":"And mainstream culture has kind of fed this idea"},{"time":32524,"text":"that hackers are people that we should be afraid of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37033,"text":"But like most things in technology"},{"time":38665,"text":"and the technology world,"},{"time":40114,"text":"hacking has equal power for good as it has for evil."},{"time":43289,"text":"For every hacker that's trying to steal your identity"},{"time":45723,"text":"there's one that's building a tool"},{"time":47961,"text":"that will help you find your\nloved ones after a disaster"},{"time":51092,"text":"or to monitor environmental quality"},{"time":54571,"text":"after an oil spill."},{"time":57308,"text":"Hacking is really just any amateur innovation"},{"time":61180,"text":"on an existing system,"},{"time":62576,"text":"and it is a deeply democratic activity."},{"time":65406,"text":"It's about critical thinking."},{"time":66805,"text":"It's about questioning existing ways of doing things."},{"time":69839,"text":"It's the idea that if you see a \nproblem, you work to fix it,"},{"time":73227,"text":"and not just complain about it."},{"time":75258,"text":"And in many ways, hacking is what built America."},{"time":79168,"text":"Betsy Ross was a hacker."},{"time":81313,"text":"The Underground Railroad was a brilliant hack."},{"time":84508,"text":"And from the Wright brothers to Steve Jobs,"},{"time":87384,"text":"hacking has always been at the foundation"},{"time":89923,"text":"of American democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92975,"text":"So if there's one thing I want\nto leave you here with today,"},{"time":97276,"text":"it's that the next time you\nthink about who a hacker is,"},{"time":99847,"text":"you think not of this guy"},{"time":103869,"text":"but of this guy, Benjamin Franklin,"},{"time":106449,"text":"who was one of the greatest hackers of all time."},{"time":109407,"text":"He was one of America's most prolific inventors,"},{"time":111548,"text":"though he famously never filed a patent,"},{"time":113730,"text":"because he thought that all human knowledge"},{"time":115324,"text":"should be freely available."},{"time":117952,"text":"He brought us bifocals and the lightning rod,"},{"time":120984,"text":"and of course there was his collaboration"},{"time":123181,"text":"on the invention of American democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126146,"text":"And in Code For America, we really try to embody"},{"time":128469,"text":"the spirit of Ben Franklin."},{"time":130487,"text":"He was a tinkerer and a statesman"},{"time":133929,"text":"whose conception of citizenship"},{"time":135789,"text":"was always predicated on action."},{"time":137876,"text":"He believed that government could be built"},{"time":140661,"text":"by the people,"},{"time":142301,"text":"and we call those people civic hackers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146850,"text":"So it's no wonder that the values"},{"time":149305,"text":"that underly a healthy democracy,"},{"time":151973,"text":"like collaboration and empowerment"},{"time":154966,"text":"and participation and enterprise,"},{"time":157029,"text":"are the same values that underly the Internet."},{"time":160515,"text":"And so it's no surprise that many hackers"},{"time":162611,"text":"are turning their attention to\nthe problem of government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165968,"text":"But before I give you a few examples"},{"time":168021,"text":"of what civic hacking looks like,"},{"time":169843,"text":"I want to make clear that you don't have"},{"time":171359,"text":"to be a programmer to be a civic hacker."},{"time":173453,"text":"You just have to believe that you can bring"},{"time":175208,"text":"a 21st-century tool set to bear"},{"time":177475,"text":"on the problems that government faces."},{"time":179914,"text":"And we hear all the time from our community"},{"time":181959,"text":"of civic hackers at Code for America"},{"time":184247,"text":"that they didn't understand\nhow much nontechnical work"},{"time":186855,"text":"actually went into civic hacking projects."},{"time":188881,"text":"So keep that in mind."},{"time":190372,"text":"All of you are potential civic hackers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194462,"text":"So what does civic hacking look like?"},{"time":196482,"text":"Our team last year in Honolulu,"},{"time":198746,"text":"which in this case was three full-time fellows"},{"time":201361,"text":"who were doing a year of public service,"},{"time":203513,"text":"were asked by the city to rebuild the website."},{"time":207478,"text":"And it's a massive thing of\ntens of thousands of pages"},{"time":210557,"text":"which just wasn't going to be possible"},{"time":212673,"text":"in the few months that they had."},{"time":214426,"text":"So instead, they decided to build a parallel site"},{"time":216883,"text":"that better conformed to how citizens actually"},{"time":219345,"text":"want to interact with information on a city website."},{"time":222684,"text":"They're looking for answers to questions,"},{"time":224621,"text":"and they want to take action when they're done,"},{"time":227247,"text":"which is really hard to do from a site"},{"time":229533,"text":"that looks like this."},{"time":231182,"text":"So our team built Honolulu Answers,"},{"time":233427,"text":"which is a super-simple search interface"},{"time":235793,"text":"where you enter a search term or a question"},{"time":238246,"text":"and get back plain language answers"},{"time":240944,"text":"that drive a user towards action."},{"time":243384,"text":"Now the site itself was easy enough to build,"},{"time":246241,"text":"but the team was faced with the challenge"},{"time":248144,"text":"of how they populate all of the content."},{"time":250854,"text":"It would have taken the three of them"},{"time":252530,"text":"a very long time,"},{"time":253907,"text":"especially given that none of \nthem are actually from Honolulu."},{"time":256906,"text":"And so they did something that's really radical,"},{"time":258981,"text":"when you think about how government"},{"time":260654,"text":"is used to working."},{"time":262695,"text":"They asked citizens to write the content."},{"time":265707,"text":"So you've heard of a hack-a-thon."},{"time":267201,"text":"They held a write-a-thon,"},{"time":268865,"text":"where on one Saturday afternoon --"},{"time":271502,"text":"(\"What do I do about wild pigs \nbeing a nuisance?\") (Laughter) â€”"},{"time":273543,"text":"Wild pigs are a huge problem \nin Honolulu, apparently."},{"time":277589,"text":"In one Saturday afternoon,"},{"time":279632,"text":"they were able to populate most of the content"},{"time":281966,"text":"for most of the frequently asked questions,"},{"time":283627,"text":"but more importantly than that,"},{"time":285860,"text":"they created a new way for citizens \nto participate in their government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289975,"text":"Now, I think this is a really cool story in and of itself,"},{"time":293020,"text":"but it gets more awesome."},{"time":295357,"text":"On the National Day of Civic Hacking"},{"time":297963,"text":"this past June in Oakland, where I live,"},{"time":300374,"text":"the Code For America team in Oakland"},{"time":302403,"text":"took the open source code base of Honolulu Answers"},{"time":304603,"text":"and turned it into Oakland Answers,"},{"time":306614,"text":"and again we held a write-a-thon"},{"time":308693,"text":"where we took the most frequently asked questions"},{"time":312041,"text":"and had citizens write the answers to them,"},{"time":313703,"text":"and I got into the act."},{"time":315172,"text":"I authored this answer, and a few others."},{"time":318773,"text":"And I'm trying to this day to articulate"},{"time":321885,"text":"the sense of empowerment and responsibility"},{"time":324931,"text":"that I feel for the place that I live"},{"time":328511,"text":"based simply on this small act of participation."},{"time":332553,"text":"And by stitching together my small act"},{"time":336278,"text":"with the thousands of other\nsmall acts of participation"},{"time":339084,"text":"that we're enabling through civic hacking,"},{"time":341665,"text":"we think we can reenergize citizenship"},{"time":344449,"text":"and restore trust in government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347499,"text":"At this point, you may be wondering"},{"time":348836,"text":"what city officials think of all this."},{"time":350562,"text":"They actually love it."},{"time":352115,"text":"As most of you guys know, cities are being asked"},{"time":354309,"text":"every day to do more with less,"},{"time":357030,"text":"and they're always looking for innovative solutions"},{"time":359228,"text":"to entrenched problems."},{"time":360962,"text":"So when you give citizens a way to participate"},{"time":364496,"text":"beyond attending a town hall meeting,"},{"time":366334,"text":"cities can actually capture"},{"time":368286,"text":"the capacity in their communities"},{"time":371040,"text":"to do the business of government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374075,"text":"Now I don't want to leave the impression"},{"time":376068,"text":"that civic hacking is just an American phenomenon."},{"time":378180,"text":"It's happening across the globe,"},{"time":379883,"text":"and one of my favorite examples"},{"time":381536,"text":"is from Mexico City, where earlier this year,"},{"time":383967,"text":"the Mexico House of Representatives"},{"time":386077,"text":"entered into a contract with\na software development firm"},{"time":390389,"text":"to build an app that legislators would use"},{"time":393569,"text":"to track bills."},{"time":394820,"text":"So this was just for the handful of legislators"},{"time":397496,"text":"in the House."},{"time":400070,"text":"And the contract was a two-year contract"},{"time":402739,"text":"for 9.3 million dollars."},{"time":406665,"text":"Now a lot of people were really angry about this,"},{"time":409017,"text":"especially geeks who knew that 9.3 million dollars"},{"time":411964,"text":"was an absolutely outrageous amount of money"},{"time":414268,"text":"for what was a very simple app."},{"time":416239,"text":"But instead of taking to the streets,"},{"time":418668,"text":"they issued a challenge."},{"time":420876,"text":"They asked programmers in Mexico"},{"time":423707,"text":"to build something better and cheaper,"},{"time":426910,"text":"and they offered a prize of 9,300 dollars --"},{"time":431361,"text":"10,000 times cheaper"},{"time":433262,"text":"than the government contract,"},{"time":434910,"text":"and they gave the entrants 10 days."},{"time":438013,"text":"And in those 10 days,"},{"time":439825,"text":"they submitted 173 apps,"},{"time":443886,"text":"five of which were presented to Congress"},{"time":446520,"text":"and are still in the app store today."},{"time":448621,"text":"And because of this action,"},{"time":450442,"text":"that contract was vacated,"},{"time":452570,"text":"and now this has sparked a movement in Mexico City"},{"time":454702,"text":"which is home to one of our partners,"},{"time":456459,"text":"Code for Mexico City."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458917,"text":"And so what you see in all three of these places,"},{"time":461668,"text":"in Honolulu and in Oakland and in Mexico City,"},{"time":464485,"text":"are the elements that are\nat the core of civic hacking."},{"time":467676,"text":"It's citizens who saw things\nthat could be working better"},{"time":470699,"text":"and they decided to fix them,"},{"time":472630,"text":"and through that work, they're creating"},{"time":474289,"text":"a 21st-century ecosystem of participation."},{"time":477480,"text":"They're creating a whole new set of ways"},{"time":479510,"text":"for citizens to be involved,"},{"time":481516,"text":"besides voting or signing a petition or protesting."},{"time":485461,"text":"They can actually build government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489438,"text":"So back to our friend Ben Franklin,"},{"time":492574,"text":"who, one of his lesser-known accomplishments"},{"time":495320,"text":"was that in 1736 he founded"},{"time":499195,"text":"the first volunteer firefighting\ncompany in Philadelphia,"},{"time":502753,"text":"called a brigade."},{"time":504452,"text":"And it's because he and his friends noticed"},{"time":506678,"text":"that the city was having trouble keeping up"},{"time":508377,"text":"with all the fires that were happening in the city,"},{"time":510447,"text":"so in true civic hacker fashion,"},{"time":513236,"text":"they built a solution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515886,"text":"And we have our own brigades at Code for America"},{"time":518396,"text":"working on the projects that I've just described,"},{"time":521542,"text":"and we want to ask you"},{"time":523280,"text":"to follow in Ben Franklin's footsteps"},{"time":525742,"text":"and come join us."},{"time":527209,"text":"We have 31 brigades in the U.S."},{"time":529499,"text":"We are pleased to announce today"},{"time":530767,"text":"that we're opening up the \nbrigade to international cities"},{"time":533043,"text":"for the first time,"},{"time":534635,"text":"starting with cities in Poland and Japan and Ireland."},{"time":538616,"text":"You can find out if there's a brigade where you live"},{"time":540715,"text":"at brigade.codeforamerica.org,"},{"time":543209,"text":"and if there's not a brigade\nwhere you live, we will help you."},{"time":545648,"text":"We've created a tool kit which also lives"},{"time":547504,"text":"at brigade.codeforamerica.org,"},{"time":549068,"text":"and we will support you along the way."},{"time":551608,"text":"Our goal is to create a global\nnetwork of civic hackers"},{"time":555523,"text":"who are innovating on the existing system"},{"time":558276,"text":"in order to build tools that will solve"},{"time":561236,"text":"entrenched problems,"},{"time":563102,"text":"that will support local government,"},{"time":565129,"text":"and that will empower citizens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566688,"text":"So please come hack with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569063,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570611,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}